# Testify Team Project Standards

## 🏗️ Project Structure

**CRITICAL**: This is a **GROUP PROJECT**. Follow the established structure strictly.

### Directory Structure

```
Testify/                    ← Server-side (ASP.NET Core)
├── Controllers/           ← API Controllers only
├── Repositories/          ← Data access layer
├── Services/             ← Server-side services (direct DB/Repository access)
├── Entities/             ← Database entities
├── Data/                 ← DbContext, User entities
├── Interfaces/           ← Repository interfaces
└── Migrations/           ← EF Core migrations

Testify.Client/            ← Client-side (Blazor WebAssembly/Server)
├── Features/             ← Feature-based organization
│   ├── {FeatureName}/
│   │   ├── Pages/       ← Razor pages for feature
│   │   ├── Components/  ← Razor components for feature
│   │   └── Services/    ← Client services (HTTP API calls)
├── Shared/
│   └── Components/      ← Shared components
└── Interfaces/          ← Client interfaces

Testify.Shared/           ← Shared code between Server & Client
├── DTOs/                ← Data Transfer Objects
├── Enums/               ← Shared enumerations
└── Helpers/             ← Shared helper classes
```

## ✅ DO's

### 1. Follow Feature-Based Organization (Client)

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD - New notification feature
Testify.Client/Features/Notifications/
├── Pages/NotificationsPage.razor
├── Components/NotificationItem.razor
└── Services/NotificationService.cs
```

### 2. Respect Service Layer Separation

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD - Server service (direct Repository access)
namespace Testify.Services
{
    public class ServerNotificationService : INotificationService
    {
        private readonly INotificationRepository _repository;
        // Direct database access via Repository
    }
}

// ✅ GOOD - Client service (HTTP calls)
namespace Testify.Client.Features.Notifications.Services
{
    public class NotificationService : INotificationService
    {
        private readonly HttpClient _httpClient;
        // HTTP API calls
    }
}
```

### 3. Use Proper Render Modes

```razor
@* ✅ GOOD - Parent component has rendermode *@
@rendermode InteractiveServer

@* Child components inherit from parent *@
<NotificationDropdown />
```

### 4. DTOs in Shared Project

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD - DTOs belong in Testify.Shared
namespace Testify.Shared.DTOs.Notifications
{
    public class NotificationResponse
    {
        public long Id { get; set; }
        public string Title { get; set; }
    }
}
```

## ❌ DON'Ts

### 1. Don't Modify Files Outside Your Feature

```
❌ BAD - Modifying unrelated features
Working on: Notifications feature
Modified:
- ✅ Testify.Client/Features/Notifications/...
- ❌ Testify.Client/Features/Projects/...      ← WRONG!
- ❌ Testify.Client/Features/Kanban/...        ← WRONG!
```

**Exception**: Only modify shared files if absolutely necessary and document why.

### 2. Don't Create Wrong Service Types

```csharp
// ❌ BAD - Server service using HttpClient
namespace Testify.Services
{
    public class SomeService
    {
        private readonly HttpClient _httpClient; // WRONG!
    }
}

// ❌ BAD - Client service accessing Repository directly
namespace Testify.Client.Features.SomeFeature.Services
{
    public class SomeService
    {
        private readonly IRepository _repository; // WRONG!
    }
}
```

### 3. Don't Break Naming Conventions

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
Controllers/notification_controller.cs
Entities/notificationEntity.cs

// ✅ GOOD
Controllers/NotificationsController.cs
Entities/Notification.cs
```

## 🎨 Code Quality Standards

### Clean Code Principles

1. **Self-documenting code**: Variable/method names should be clear
2. **Single Responsibility**: Each class/method does ONE thing
3. **DRY**: Don't Repeat Yourself
4. **Consistent formatting**: Follow existing patterns

### Example

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
public async Task<List<NotificationResponse>> Get(string id)
{
    var x = await _repo.GetUserNotificationsAsync(id);
    return x.ToList();
}

// ✅ GOOD
public async Task<List<NotificationResponse>> GetNotificationsAsync(string userId)
{
    var notifications = await _notificationRepository.GetUserNotificationsAsync(userId);
    return notifications.ToList();
}
```

## 🔧 When Making Changes

**Before coding, ask yourself:**

1. ✅ Is this change within my assigned feature?
2. ✅ Am I following the existing directory structure?
3. ✅ Am I using the correct service type (Server vs Client)?
4. ✅ Have I checked for similar patterns in the codebase?
5. ✅ Will this change affect other team members' work?

**If unsure, DON'T modify - ask the team first!**

## 📝 Migration & Database

```bash
# Create migration
dotnet ef migrations add MigrationName --project Testify/Testify.csproj

# Apply migration
dotnet ef database update --project Testify/Testify.csproj
```

**Always test migrations locally before committing!**

## 🚀 Summary

- **Follow the tree structure**: Don't create new top-level folders
- **Stay in your lane**: Only modify files related to your feature
- **Match existing patterns**: Look at similar features for guidance
- **Clean code**: Write maintainable, readable code
- **Test before commit**: Ensure your changes don't break existing functionality
